title: Little Pick Energy
description: Fun-loving weirdos, incorrigible min-maxers, folks who enjoy playing with puzzles, pushing boundaries, and picking the occasional lock: do you have Little Pick Energy? CollateralTech sure has! Instead of filming for Green Belt, CT has been up late laboring out of love and lunacy, trying to jam over two dozen locksport tools into a condom wrapper...
descriptionContinued: The result? A nifty fifty-fifty mixture of hooks and rakes with enough tools to cover most basic pin-tumbler locks and then some. The condom wrapper idea didn't pan out, but the finished package easily fits inside an American 1100 box. Put your RAFL tickets down to win some locks, some fun swag, and an updated copy of CT's original pint-sized passion project, the Stuffed Sparrow.

title: The Paladin
description:
(Photo pending)
*Town Crier enters.* Hear ye, hear ye! Good peoples of the lockpicking guild, lend thine ears to this proclamation most grand! By order of chance and fortune, a prize of noble bearing shall be drawn in our raffle. Behold! “The Paladin”...
descriptionContinued: A mat of steadfast craft, upon which the worthy locksmith may lay their tools, keeping order and honor in their practice. Two flags of matching heraldry, proud tokens to mark thy implements, that all may know thee as a knight of the pick and pin. This treasure stands as guardian of thy craft, a companion in every noble endeavor of locks and keys. Step forth, take thy chance, and may fortune’s warded gate swing wide for thee!

title: A Box of Skittles
description: While this may look just exactly like a very ordinary box of Skittles, the truth is that this rainbow contains cleverly hidden secrets that will last you far longer than any other Skittles you’ll ever come across! Don’t put them in your mouth; they’re too large for that and won’t do your teeth any favors...
descriptionContinued: While some people may enjoy them by blindly taking one at random, others find it more pleasing to line them up like an OCD person and methodically complete one color before moving on to the next. I personally found each of these to be a good experience and would recommend this pot for a beginner to intermediate picker looking for a broad experience ascending the ranks.
